A 42-year-old businessman, Augustine Eze, yesterday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly macheting a man. Eze, who lives in Isolo, allegedly committed the offence on August 24 at Isolo. Prosecuting Sergeant Kendrich Nomayo said the accused attacked the complainant, Mr Moses Ebonwyi, with a machete during a misunderstanding. “The accused approached the complainant with a machete and cut his left leg, causing him grievous harm,” he said. The accused pleaded not guilt. Magistrate T.O Ojo granted the accused N100,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. Mrs Ojo said the sureties should be employed and show evidence of two years tax payment. She adjourned till September 27.